inlineContent.text: Core Data supports the following attribute types, which differentiate between bit sizes to enable data-store independence. For some types, a scalar option is available.
If your application uses Binary Large Objects (BLOBs) like image and sound data, prefer to store its binary data outside of the Core Data store.
